           <h1>Terms &amp; Conditions</h1> 
           <h2>1. ACCEPTANCE OF TERMS</h2> 
           <p>This site ("Site") is made available to you, subject to the following Terms of Service ("TOS"), which may be modified from time to time at the sole discretion of BuffaloNews.com. The "Site" includes the Buffalonews.com, and all such pages, information, data, text, software, music, sound, photographs, graphics, video, messages or any other material or content on the Site. Modified TOS will become effective immediately upon posting. By accessing this Site you agree to be bound by the TOS and any modifications made thereto. </p> 
           <p>You understand and agree that the Site is provided "AS-IS" and that Buffalonews.com assumes no responsibility for the timeliness, deletion, misdelivery or failure to store any user communications or personalization settings. </p> 
           <p>These TOS shall be applicable to all features of the Site. Any additional rules or guidelines posted in any of the features of the Site shall be equally applicable and shall be considered as being incorporated by reference into these TOS. In the case of a conflict between the TOS and any other rules, guidelines or policies, the TOS shall control unless specified otherwise. </p> 
           <p> These TOS shall be applicable regardless of how the Site is accessed, including but not limited to mobile sites and applications, RSS, API, or in any other manner, whether now known or developed in the future. </p> 
           <p> References to the Buffalonews.com includes The Buffalo News Inc., its parent, subsidiary and affiliated companies. </p> 
           <p> At the sole discretion of Buffalonews.com, Service features, content and databases may be altered, discontinued or suspended and limits may be imposed on certain features and services including, but not limited to, restricting access to all or part of the Services without notice or liability. </p> 
           <h2>2. COPYRIGHT AND COPYRIGHT COMPLAINTS</h2> 
           <p>All information, content, services and software displayed on, transmitted through, or used in connection with the Site, including but not limited to news articles, reviews, directories, guides, text, photographs, images, illustrations, audio clips, video, html, source and object code, trademarks, logos, and the like, as well as its selection, layout and arrangement (collectively, the "Content"), is owned by The Buffalo News, Inc., and its affiliated companies, licensors and suppliers. The Buffalo News Inc., its affiliated companies, licensors and suppliers, exclusively own all right, title and interest (including but not limited to all copyright interest) to such Content, with all rights Reserved. You may use the Content for your occasional personal, non-commercial use, provided you do not remove any trademark, copyright or other notices from such Content. No other use is permitted without prior written permission of Buffalonews.com. The permitted use described in this paragraph is contingent on your compliance at all times with the TOS. You must abide by all additional copyright notices, information, or restrictions contained in any Content accessed through the Site.</p> 
           <p>The Site has been specially designed for presentation of Content in a unique format and appearance. We are concerned about the integrity of our Site when it is viewed in a setting created by a third party that includes advertising or other material that we have not authorized to be displayed on our Site. Without limiting the provisions of the above paragraph, neither you nor any third party shall make use of the Content in any manner that constitutes an infringement of our rights, including copyright. You may not, for example, republish any portion of the Content on any Internet, Intranet or Extranet site or incorporate Content in, or use the Content to construct any database, compilation or archive. You may not modify, sell, publish, transmit, display or otherwise use in any public or commercial manner any portion of the Content. You may not frame or utilize framing techniques that involve any Content or portion of the Site or suggest any relationship between our Site and you without our express written consent. You may not scrape our Content or our Site. You agree not to: decompile, reverse engineer or disassemble any software or other products or processes accessible through the Site, or insert any code or product or manipulate the Content or Site in any way that affects the user's experience, or use any data mining, data gathering, or data mining extractions method with respect to the Content or Site, or use any cancel bots or Trojan horses in connection with your use of the Site.</p> 
           <p> Requests to use Content for any purpose other than as permitted in the TOS must be directed to The Buffalo News, One News Plaza, P.O. Box 100, Buffalo, NY 14240; (716) 849-4444; <a href="comments@Buffalonews.com">comments@Buffalonews.com</a>. If you do not seek and obtain such authorization, you should assume no third party has the right to allow you to use the Content. </p> 
           <h2>3. YOUR REGISTRATION OBLIGATIONS</h2> 
           <p>In consideration of your use of the site, you agree to: (a) provide true, accurate, current and complete information about yourself as prompted by the Site's registration form (such information being the "Registration Data") and (b) maintain and promptly update the registration Data to keep it true, accurate, current and complete. The decision to provide this information is strictly optional. However, if you elect not to provide such information, you may not be able to access certain Content or participate in various areas of the Site. Using a name other than your own is strictly prohibited. If you provide any information that is untrue, inaccurate, not current or incomplete, or Buffalonews.com has reasonable grounds to suspect such information is untrue, inaccurate, not current or incomplete, Buffalonews.com has the right to suspend or terminate your account and refuse any and all current or future use of the Site (or any portion thereof). Please remember that the Site is designed to appeal to a broad audience. </p> 
           <p> You must be at least thirteen years of age to register to use the site. If you are the parent or legal guardian of a child under thirteen it is your responsibility to determine whether the Site and/or Content is appropriate for your minor child and you are encouraged to monitor their access. </p> 
           <h2>4. BUFFALONEWS.COM PRIVACY POLICY</h2> 
           <p>Registration data and certain other information about you are subject to our Privacy Policy. For more information, please review our entire Privacy Policy. In the case of a conflict between the TOS and the terms of any other policy, including the Privacy Policy, the TOS shall control unless specified otherwise. Subject to your right to discontinue receipt, Buffalonews.com may send you electronic mail concerning the Site, specific features and products, and/or information that may be of interest to you. Buffalonews.com may contact you by email regarding your participation in surveys, asking for feedback about the Site or existing products or services. This information will be used to improve our Site and better understand our users. Any information obtained in such surveys will not be shared with third parties, except in aggregate form.</p> 
           <h2>5. MEMBER ACCOUNT, PASSWORD AND SECURITY</h2> 
           <p>You will receive a password and account designation upon completing the Site's registration process. You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of the password and account, and are fully responsible for all activities that occur under your password or account. You agree to immediately notify Buffalonews.com of any unauthorized use of your password or account or any other breach of security, and you agree not to sell, transfer or assign your account, password or associated rights. You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your password and for restricting access to your computer so that unauthorized users may not access the Site using your name, account designation or password.</p> 
           <h2>6. USER SUBMISSION</h2> 
           <p>Should you send any materials, idea, or content of any nature, including but not limited to photographs, documents, blog posts, and comments (collectively, "User Submission") to Buffalonews.com, you do so with the understanding that no consideration of any sort will be provided to you, and you are hereby waiving any claim against Buffalonews.com and its affiliates regarding the Use (as defined below) of any User Submission.</p> 
